Field Description Success Message The exact value your provider's API returns in a successful response to indicate the message was accepted, for example <code>success</code> Response ID Key The name of the field in the provider's response body that contains the provider's own message identifier, for example <code>response_id</code> <p>A Response Sample panel shows a representative JSON success response — for example:</p> <pre><code>{
  "status": "success",
  "message": "Message sent successfully to the user",
  "response_id": "1545124"
}
</code></pre> <p>Selecting Copy JSON copies this sample to the clipboard, which is useful when sharing the expected response format with a provider's technical support team during onboarding.</p>

Field Description Error Code Key The name of the field in the provider's response body that contains the error code, for example <code>status_code</code> Error Message Key The name of the field that contains the human-readable error description, for example <code>message</code> <p>As with the Success Response tab, an Error Sample panel shows a representative JSON error response, for example:</p> <pre><code>{
  "status": "failed",
  "message": "Error Occured",
  "status_code": 403
}
</code></pre> <p>The error codes referenced here are the same codes you configure for automatic retry behavior in Error and Retry Management — Response Mapping tells Equify where to find the error code in the provider's response, while Error and Retry Management tells Equify what to do once it has found it.</p>
